Java Exceptions

What: Errors that occur when your Java program runs.

Types of Java Exceptions

1️⃣ Checked Exceptions

    Must be handled (try-catch or throws)

    *   IOException – error in input/output
    *   FileNotFoundException – file not found
    *   SQLException – database error
    *   ClassNotFoundException – class not found

2️⃣ Unchecked Exceptions (Runtime Exceptions)

    Occur at runtime

    *   NullPointerException – accessing a null object
    *   ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException – wrong array index
    *   ArithmeticException – divide by zero
    *   NumberFormatException – string to number conversion error
    *   IllegalArgumentException – invalid argument
    *   IllegalStateException – method called at the wrong time
    *   ClassCastException – invalid type casting

====================================================================================================

Selenium Exceptions

What: Errors when automating a browser with Selenium.

    *   NoSuchElementException – element not found
    *   ElementNotVisibleException - Element is present in DOM but not visible.
    *   ElementNotSelectableException - Element is present but can’t be selected.
    *   StaleElementReferenceException - Element is no longer attached to the DOM.
    *   NoSuchFrameException - Frame not found.
    *   TimeoutException – wait times out
    *   NoSuchWindowException - Window not found.
    *   NoAlertPresentException - Alert not found.

    Why: Often because of page load issues, missing elements, or dynamic pages.

====================================================================================================

Cucumber Exceptions

What: Errors when using Cucumber for BDD testing.

   Examples:
   *    UndefinedStepException – step in feature file not defined
   *    AmbiguousStepDefinitionsException – multiple matching step definitions

   Why: Happens when steps are missing or duplicated in step definitions.
